    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1d-j: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence staining for DOCK4, PSD95 (DLG4) and synaptophysin (SYP) in hippocampal neurons showed localization of DOCK4 to the postsynapse.\n\nFigure 2d-g, 3: shRNA knockdown of DOCK4 in hippocampal neurons impaired dendritic spine formation. Specific shRNA targeting DOCK4 domains showed that the GEF activity and the proline-rich region are required for Dock4-mediated spine formation.\n\nauthors conclude: \"These results suggest that Dock4 positively regulates dendritic spine formation through activation of Rac in hippocampal neurons.\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"Subcellular localization of Dock4 in hippocampal neurons. (A-C) Frozen coronal sections of postnatal day 20 rat brain were incubated with anti-Dock4 antibody, anti-MAP2 antibody, and phalloidin to stain F-actin.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"a mouse monoclonal antibody against Dock4 used for immunoblotting and immunostaining (R6Y; Supplemental Figure S1B)\"",
